The Trek4Mandela team of climbers have arrived in Tanzania for this year's Kilimanjaro expedition. The climbers left the country on Tuesday evening. This morning, they will start their ascent of the mountain. #DStv403 DODOMA - The Trek4Mandela team of climbers have arrived in Tanzania for this year's Kilimanjaro expedition. The climbers left the country on Tuesday evening. GALLERY | Meet the Trek4Mandela team On Thursday morning they will start their ascent of the mountain. The annual expedition to reach Africa’s highest peak on Mandela Day is celebrating its 10th anniversary. WATCH: Trek4Mandela | 'The milestone climb' It brings together inspired individuals to raise funds and create awareness for the Caring4Girls programme. The Trek4Mandela climbers will be led by Sibusiso Vilane, the first Black African to conquer the Three Poles challenge, which is reaching the North and South Poles and Mount Everest.